          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Soak the dates, 10 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 170°C fan. Butter and line the loaf tin. Put the {{dates-medjool}} and {{unsalted-butter}} in a large bowl. Pour the boiling {{water}} over them and stir briefly. Leave for 10 minutes. This is the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "fruit soaking",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9ygj3t0000z8v4s6wbl7zs"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": the dates will absorb the water and partially dissolve; the butter will melt into the liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add the {{dark-brown-sugar}}, {{black-treacle}}, and beaten {{eggs}} to the date mixture and stir to combine. Add the {{plain-flour}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}} and stir until just smooth. Fold in the {{walnuts}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 50 to 55 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the batter into the prepared tin. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes until a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean. The top will be very dark, this is expected. If it is browning too quickly before the centre is set, lay a piece of foil loosely over the top. Cool in the tin for 15 minutes before turning out. Slice thick.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
